<br>
the best size of tablet is a very individual thing as it depends 100% of your way of drawing/painting etc...<br>
4x5 works fine for people just using their finger musculature for moving the pen. there is no need for lots of space because these people are used to draw small scaled.<br>
now think about a painter who is used to work on higher formats. he will die in front of a 4x5 because he wants to use his whole arm and doesn't have enough space for.<br>
<br>
i looked at several pieces i did and they all were about the size of 6x8 tablet. i bought one and it's the best working solution for me, as i tried smaller ones too(at friends).<br>
